Package co.cask.cdap.api.dataset.table

Provides access to the system-level table Datasets available within CDAP.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Filter
    Filter to be applied to Scan.
    MemoryTable
    A Table that stores all data in memory.
    OrderedTable Deprecated
    since 2.8.0.
    Row
    Represents one row in a table with a subset of columns.
    Scanner
    Interface for table scan operation.
    Table
    An ordered, optionally explorable, named table.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Delete
    A Delete removes one or more or all columns from a row.
    EmptyRow
    Represents an empty row (a row with no columns).
    Get
    A Get reads one, multiple, or all columns of a row.
    Increment
    An Increment interprets the values of columns as 8-byte integers and increments them by the specified value.
    Put
    Writes the specified value(s) in one or more columns of a row -- this overrides existing values.
    Result
    Default implementation of Row
    RowColumns<T>
    Base class for defining a row with set of columns.
    Scan
    Scan configuration for Table.
    Tables
    Utility for describing Table and derived data sets within application configuration.
    TableSplit
    Table splits are simply a start and stop key.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ConflictDetection
    Conflict detection level of a table.
